# 2025-11-21 15:32:27.430872
+Create a full-screen mobile-friendly 3D Minecraft clone using only a single Next.js page with vanilla Three.js from CDN (no npm installs).
+
+Requirements:
+- Use https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/three@0.169.0/build/three.min.js and https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/three@0.169.0/examples/js/controls/PointerLockControls.js via <script> tags in app/layout.tsx or page.tsx
+- Infinite procedural terrain using SimplexNoise (also from CDN: https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/simplex-noise@4.0.1/simplex-noise.js)
+- Chunk system (16x16x64), greedy meshing or at least face culling
+- First-person controls:
+  - Mobile: left half screen = virtual joystick for movement, right half = drag to look
+  - Desktop: WASD + mouse (PointerLockControls fallback)
+- Tap/click to break block, right-click or long-tap to place block (grass block for now)
+- Player physics: gravity, jumping, collision with blocks
+- Day lighting + fog
+- Black terminal style UI overlay with crosshair
+- Store player position in localStorage
+- No external dependencies beyond the three CDN scripts
+- Fix any syntax errors and make sure it builds and runs perfectly in MiniApp Factory
+- Make it look and feel like real Minecraft, 60 FPS on iPhone/Android

